hard drive defragment i tried the defragment option of the pc but after i did a defragment and it finished i pressed analyze and it said that it needs a defragment whats the problem if you reboot into safe mode and clear up temporary internet files or any other temporary files and then do a defrag in safe mode it will do it slightly faster as no other services or background apps are running and it will be cleaner and easier to do the defrag then start in normal mode and it should be fine Windows 2000 Windows XP Defrag Virtual memory FreeDOS File system Redundant array of independent disks System/36 Windows 95 Mach kernel MiniDisc Pump It Up AmigaOS C programming language System/34 Internet Relay Chat Universal Serial Bus Floppy disk Beatmania IIDX Hard disk Mouse (computing) Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Microsoft Windows Garbage collection (computer science) Windows registry Carburetor Windows Server 2003 Blue screen of death Ext3 IBM PC compatible Enterprise content management Resident Evil 2 NeXT Atari 8-bit family Linux Booting Norton Utilities Emacs E85 IPod Toyota Prius Windows Vista Dance Dance Revolution Apple IIGS NX bit Drill bit Diablo II: Lord of Destruction GunZ The Duel Computer virus Palm OS USB flash drive Mod (computer gaming) PNG Windows Me REBOL Advance Wars: Dual Strike Anchor Amiga Mac OS 8 Super Nintendo Entertainment System Knoppix Digital circuit Gravity Probe B File Transfer Protocol Mozilla Firefox Thread (computer science) E-mail Motorcycle Embedded system In The Groove (game) Normal distribution Vi Data General Nova RISC Cheating in Counter-Strike Control-Alt-Delete Gameplay of StarCraft ReiserFS ALGOL 68 BZFlag Ethernet Apple II family M16 (rifle) MS-DOS CPU design Common Unix Printing System Novell NetWare Sonic R Windows 3.x VMware Ashton-Tate WordStar Bluetooth Gradius Macromedia Flash Sonic the Hedgehog 2 IBM PC Simple Mail Transfer Protocol Minesweeper (computer game) 